org.opendaylight.controller.networkconfig.neutron

Interface INeutronSecurityGroupAware


  • public interface INeutronSecurityGroupAware
    This interface defines the methods a service that wishes to be aware of Neutron Security Groups needs to implement

    • Method Detail

      • canCreateNeutronSecurityGroup

        int canCreateNeutronSecurityGroup(NeutronSecurityGroup securityGroup)
        Services provide this interface method to indicate if the specified security group can be created
        Parameters:
        securityGroup - instance of proposed new Neutron Security Group object
        Returns:
        integer the return value is understood to be a HTTP status code. A return value outside of 200 through 299 results in the create operation being interrupted and the returned status value reflected in the HTTP response.

      • neutronSecurityGroupCreated

        void neutronSecurityGroupCreated(NeutronSecurityGroup securityGroup)
        Services provide this interface method for taking action after a security group has been created
        Parameters:
        securityGroup - instance of new Neutron Security Group object

      • canUpdateNeutronSecurityGroup

        int canUpdateNeutronSecurityGroup(NeutronSecurityGroup delta,
                                NeutronSecurityGroup original)
        Services provide this interface method to indicate if the specified security group can be changed using the specified delta
        Parameters:
        delta - updates to the security group object using patch semantics
        original - instance of the Neutron Security Group object to be updated
        Returns:
        integer the return value is understood to be a HTTP status code. A return value outside of 200 through 299 results in the update operation being interrupted and the returned status value reflected in the HTTP response.

      • neutronSecurityGroupUpdated

        void neutronSecurityGroupUpdated(NeutronSecurityGroup securityGroup)
        Services provide this interface method for taking action after a security group has been updated
        Parameters:
        securityGroup - instance of modified Neutron Security Group object

      • canDeleteNeutronSecurityGroup

        int canDeleteNeutronSecurityGroup(NeutronSecurityGroup securityGroup)
        Services provide this interface method to indicate if the specified security group can be deleted
        Parameters:
        securityGroup - instance of the Neutron Security Group object to be deleted
        Returns:
        integer the return value is understood to be a HTTP status code. A return value outside of 200 through 299 results in the delete operation being interrupted and the returned status value reflected in the HTTP response.

      • neutronSecurityGroupDeleted

        void neutronSecurityGroupDeleted(NeutronSecurityGroup securityGroup)

        Parameters:
        securityGroup - instance of deleted Neutron Security Group object
